This paper focuses on software performance analysis and visualization, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also discusses the use of real-time profiling, which involves analyzing program execution as it happens, and this could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or software development (cs.SD). The visualization aspect of the paper could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or other visualization-related sub-categories (cs.OH).
